Happy to announce the successful completion of 16 dynamic young ladies in Season 3 of WE Women Leaders – a focused intervention for high-potential women at managerial levels to augment their professional growth and gender equity in the workplace. 

The ladies embarked on an innovative journey of self-discovery designed with the intent of raising aspiration levels, building confidence, overcoming social inhibitions and finding a refreshed perspective on career, life & leadership. A structured mentoring program identified experienced leaders as internal mentors and created learning opportunities through handholding, experience sharing, advice and guidance. They now join 41 young women leaders who have completed the program so far, across two previous seasons.

All participants, mentors, managers joined the felicitation and shared their experiences.  The CHRO, Mr GR Venkatesh addressed the audience on the essence and relevance of the program. This was followed by a Fireside Chat with Ms. Jyoti Deshpande (CEO, Viacom18 Media Pvt. Ltd) & Ms. Savithri Parekh (Company Secretary & Compliance officer, Reliance Industries Ltd) who gave the audience an perspective on “how to make a mark in the corporate world” sharing insights from their remarkably inspirational and successful career journey
The group is looking forward to the Beginning of a New Journey….!

#RelianceRetail #WeWomen #GPTW #bestplacetowork #growthislife #retail #gptwcertified

Dillip has been an integral part of Reliance Jewels for over six years. Starting as the Store Incharge at the Bhubaneswar store, he progressed to the role of Floor Manager, and now leads as the Showroom Manager in Rourkela. He attributes his growth to the unwavering support of his seniors, whose guidance empowered him to overcome challenges with confidence. Dillip’s dedication, passion, and willingness to learn have defined his journey. The RAPID program (Reliance Jewels' Advanced Program for Integrated Development), designed for Floor Managers to advance to Showroom Managers, further enhanced his leadership skills, equipping him with strategic thinking, problem-solving abilities, and effective communication. Dillip continues to inspire his peers, setting a remarkable example of hard work, commitment, and growth within the organization.
 
#RelianceRetail #Retail #LifeAtRelianceRetail #Success #Growth #RPeopleRSuccess #People #Journey #RelianceJewels

Manisha began her journey with 7-Eleven as an Associate, quickly becoming a favorite among customers for her cheerful nature and warm attitude. Her exceptional customer service made clients feel valued, creating an inviting atmosphere that encouraged loyalty and repeat visits. With her remarkable ability to connect and engage, Manisha consistently enhanced the overall customer experience. Her friendly attitude and attentive approach set her apart, earning admiration from both customers and colleagues. Through the iAspire Step-up Program, which prepares associates for leadership roles by training them as Shift Incharges, Store Managers, and Area Managers Manisha’s dedication and hard work were recognized. She is now a Shift Incharge, inspiring her team with her excellence.

Subhayan joined Reliance Trends as a Department Manager in 2018 and swiftly climbed the ranks to become a Store Manager. The Store Leadership Development Program (SLDP) played a pivotal role in his growth, enhancing his time management, task prioritization, and analytical skills. It also refined his leadership and multitasking abilities, empowering him to master store operations. Subhayan tackled challenges such as manpower management, resolving customer issues, boosting footfall through marketing, increasing sales, and managing vendors and stakeholders. Personally, he evolved into a dynamic leader and entrepreneur, transforming his store into a thriving profit centre. Subhayan's journey reflects his unwavering commitment to excellence and growth within Reliance Trends.
 
#RelianceRetail #Retail #LifeAtRelianceRetail #Success #Growth #RPeopleRSuccess #People #Journey #RelianceTrends
